        <description>
            <geninfo>
                <para>9200, 9400 Vision 98 Chatham-produced Models built between June 28, 1996 and October 23, 1996, and
                    9800 Springfield-produced Model built between March 4, 1996 and November 11, 1996, with Detroit
                    Diesel Series 60 Engines and air conditioning are susceptible to refrigerant compressor belt loss
                    due to an angular out of alignment condition and compressor belt vibration.
                </para>
                <para>All
                    <emph type="bold">9200, 9400 Vision 98</emph>
                    Chatham-produced vehicles built between June 28, 1996 and September 19, 1996 equipped with Detroit
                    Diesel Series 60 engines will require
                    <emph type="bold">all</emph>
                    components of the retrofit kit.
                </para>
                <para>9200, 9400 Vision 98 vehicles built between September 19, 1996 and October 23, 1996
                    <emph type="bold">will not</emph>
                    require the use of the studs, washers, and nuts, but will require all other kit components.
                </para>
                <para>All
                    <emph type="bold">9800</emph>
                    Springfield-produced vehicles built between March 4, 1996 and September 26, 1996 equipped with
                    Detroit Diesel Series 60 engines will require
                    <emph type="bold">all</emph>
                    components of the retrofit kit.
                </para>
                <para>9800 vehicles built between September 26, 1996 and November 11, 1996
                    <emph type="bold">will not</emph>
                    require the use of studs, washers, and nuts, but will require all other kit components.
                </para>
                <para>This authorized field change provides the parts and service procedure to improve belt tracking and
                    increase belt frequency dampening to prevent refrigerant compressor belt loss.
                </para>
            </geninfo>
        </description>
